programme.title: NFL Playoff: Tennessee Titans at Kansas City Chiefs
programme.sub-title: Tennessee Titans at Kansas City Chiefs
programme.desc: Tennessee Titans (9-7) at Kansas City Chiefs (10-6) in an AFC wild-card game. From Arrowhead Stadium. K.C. boasts NFL rushing king Kareem Hunt and a plus-14 home turnover ratio. QB Marcus Mariota and the Titans pulled out a 19-17 win here in Dec. 2016, getting a walk-off 53-yard field goal from ex-Chief Ryan Succop. K.C. has dropped its last five home playoff games (last won after 1993 season), while Tennessee is making its first postseason appearance in nine years. (cc).(n)

programme.title: NFL Playoff: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings
programme.sub-title: New Orleans Saints at Minnesota Vikings
programme.desc: New Orleans Saints (12-5) at Minnesota Vikings (13-3) in an NFC Divisional game. From U.S. Bank Stadium. Mike Zimmer's Vikings opened 2017 with a 29-19 win over New Orleans, keeping QB Drew Brees and Co. out of the end zone until the last two minutes. Everson Griffen and Xavier Rhodes head Minnesota's defense, while the Saints boast a Pro Bowl RB tandem in Alvin Kamara and Mark Ingram. The Vikes' last playoff win was eight years ago, followed by an NFC title-game loss to the Saints. (cc).(n)

programme.title: NFL Playoff: Jacksonville Jaguars at New England Patriots
programme.sub-title: Jacksonville Jaguars at New England Patriots
programme.desc: Jacksonville Jaguars at New England Patriots in the AFC championship game. From Gillette Stadium. Bill Belichick's Pats are in their seventh straight AFC title game and are 7-4 in the game since Jacksonville's last appearance 18 years ago. The Jags' top-ranked defense allowed a season-high 545 yards in beating Pittsburgh, while New England posted its highest yards gained (vs. the Titans) since Week 2. Tom Brady is 7-0 all-time vs. the Jaguars. (cc).(n)
